# Rhino Blueprint — AI Guide

> This file teaches AI assistants (Claude, ChatGPT, Cursor, etc.) how to generate Rhino Blueprint YAML files for this project. When asked to create a new model/resource, follow this guide.

## What is Rhino Blueprint?

Rhino Blueprint is a **zero-token deterministic code generator**. You define your data model and permission matrix in YAML spec files, then run `php artisan rhino:blueprint` to generate fully working:

- **Model** — with fillable, validation rules, query builder config, traits
- **Migration** — column definitions, indexes, foreign keys
- **Factory** — faker definitions per column type
- **Scope** — auto-discovery scope file
- **Policy** — **fully working** role-based `permittedAttributesForShow/Create/Update` and `hiddenAttributesForShow` methods
- **Tests** — CRUD access (200/403), field visibility, forbidden field tests
- **RoleSeeder** — `Role::firstOrCreate()` for each role
- **UserRoleSeeder** — sample users with aggregated permissions from all models

No AI tokens are consumed during generation. The YAML spec is the single source of truth.

---

## Directory Structure

```
project-root/
  .rhino/
    blueprints/
      _roles.yaml              # Global role definitions (required)
      contracts.yaml           # Model spec + permissions
      alerts.yaml              # Model spec + permissions
      ...
      .blueprint-manifest.json # Auto-generated hash tracking
    BLUEPRINT.md               # This file (AI guide)
```

- `_roles.yaml` — prefixed with underscore, always processed first
- Model files use the **slug** as filename (snake_case, e.g., `blog_posts.yaml`)
- `.blueprint-manifest.json` — auto-managed, tracks file hashes to skip unchanged specs

---

## How to Generate a Blueprint YAML File

### Questions You MUST Ask the User

Before generating a blueprint YAML file, ask the user these questions:

1. **What is the model name?** (PascalCase singular, e.g., `Contract`, `BlogPost`)
2. **What columns/fields does it have?** For each column, ask:
   - Name (snake_case)
   - Type (see Column Types below)
   - Is it nullable?
   - Is it unique?
   - Should it be filterable/sortable/searchable?
   - Default value (if any)
3. **Does it belong to an organization?** (multi-tenant — adds `organization_id` FK)
4. **Should it use soft deletes?** (default: yes)
5. **Should it have audit trail?** (change logging)
6. **What relationships does it have?** (belongsTo, hasMany, hasOne, belongsToMany)
7. **For each role defined in `_roles.yaml`:**
   - What CRUD actions can this role perform? (index, show, store, update, destroy, trashed, restore, forceDelete)
   - Which fields can this role **see** (show_fields)?
   - Which fields can this role **create** (create_fields)?
   - Which fields can this role **update** (update_fields)?
   - Which fields should be **hidden** from this role (hidden_fields)?
8. **Are there any actions to exclude entirely?** (except_actions — blocks action for ALL roles)
9. **Should pagination be enabled?** (and how many per page?)

### Before You Generate

- Read `_roles.yaml` to know which roles exist
- Read existing blueprint files to understand patterns used in this project
- Use YAML anchors (`&name` / `*name`) to avoid duplicating field lists shared between roles

---

## YAML Format Reference

### `_roles.yaml` — Global Roles

```yaml
roles:
  owner:
    name: Owner
    description: "Full access. Manages plan, billing, users."
  admin:
    name: Admin
    description: "Operational admin. Manages users, settings."
  viewer:
    name: Viewer
    description: "Read-only access."
```

**Rules:**
- Role slugs must be lowercase with underscores only (e.g., `team_lead`)
- Each role must have a `name`
- `description` is optional but recommended

### Model Blueprint — Full Example

```yaml
model: Contract
slug: contracts          # optional — auto-derived as snake_case plural of model name
# table: contracts       # optional — defaults to slug

options:
  belongs_to_organization: true    # adds organization_id FK, scoping
  soft_deletes: true               # default: true
  audit_trail: false               # default: false
  # owner: null                    # for child models: owner: contract
  # except_actions: []             # actions to block entirely for ALL roles
  # pagination: false              # default: false
  # per_page: 25                   # default: 25

columns:
  # Short syntax — just type:
  title: string

  # Full syntax — with options:
  counterparty_cnpj:
    type: string
    nullable: true

  total_value:
    type: decimal
    nullable: true
    precision: 10
    scale: 2
    sortable: true

  status:
    type: string
    nullable: false
    default: "draft"
    filterable: true
    sortable: true

  risk_score:
    type: integer
    nullable: true
    sortable: true

  ai_summary:
    type: text
    nullable: true

  tags:
    type: json
    nullable: true

  uploaded_by:
    type: foreignId
    foreign_model: User

relationships:
  - type: belongsTo
    model: User
    foreign_key: uploaded_by       # optional — inferred from column name

  - type: hasMany
    model: Alert

permissions:
  owner:
    actions: [index, show, store, update, destroy, trashed, restore, forceDelete]
    show_fields: "*"               # wildcard — all fields
    create_fields: "*"
    update_fields: "*"

  admin:
    actions: [index, show, store, update, destroy, trashed, restore]
    show_fields: "*"
    create_fields: &admin_writable   # YAML anchor for reuse
      - title
      - status
      - counterparty_cnpj
      - total_value
      - tags
    update_fields: *admin_writable   # YAML alias — same list

  viewer:
    actions: [index, show]
    show_fields:
      - id
      - title
      - status
      - tags
    create_fields: []                # empty — cannot create
    update_fields: []                # empty — cannot update
    hidden_fields:                   # fields to explicitly hide
      - counterparty_cnpj
      - total_value
      - risk_score
```

---

## Column Types

| Type | Description | Migration | Faker |
|------|-------------|-----------|-------|
| `string` | VARCHAR(255) | `$table->string('name')` | `fake()->sentence(3)` |
| `text` | TEXT | `$table->text('name')` | `fake()->paragraph()` |
| `integer` | INT | `$table->integer('name')` | `fake()->numberBetween(1, 100)` |
| `bigInteger` | BIGINT | `$table->bigInteger('name')` | `fake()->numberBetween(1, 10000)` |
| `boolean` | BOOL | `$table->boolean('name')` | `fake()->boolean()` |
| `date` | DATE | `$table->date('name')` | `fake()->date()` |
| `datetime` | DATETIME | `$table->datetime('name')` | `fake()->dateTime()` |
| `timestamp` | TIMESTAMP | `$table->timestamp('name')` | `fake()->dateTime()` |
| `decimal` | DECIMAL(p,s) | `$table->decimal('name', p, s)` | `fake()->randomFloat(2, 0, 1000)` |
| `float` | FLOAT | `$table->float('name')` | `fake()->randomFloat(2, 0, 1000)` |
| `json` | JSON | `$table->json('name')` | `[]` |
| `uuid` | UUID | `$table->uuid('name')` | `fake()->uuid()` |
| `foreignId` | BIGINT + FK | `$table->foreignId('name')->constrained()` | `Model::factory()` |

### Column Options

| Option | Type | Default | Description |
|--------|------|---------|-------------|
| `type` | string | `string` | Column type (see above) |
| `nullable` | bool | `false` | Allow NULL values |
| `unique` | bool | `false` | Add unique constraint |
| `index` | bool | `false` | Add database index |
| `default` | mixed | `null` | Default value |
| `filterable` | bool | `false` | Allow filtering in API queries |
| `sortable` | bool | `false` | Allow sorting in API queries |
| `searchable` | bool | `false` | Include in full-text search |
| `precision` | int | `8` | Decimal precision (decimal type only) |
| `scale` | int | `2` | Decimal scale (decimal type only) |
| `foreign_model` | string | `null` | Related model name (foreignId type only) |

---

## Permission Surfaces

Each role defines 4 permission surfaces:

| Surface | Purpose | Wildcard | Empty |
|---------|---------|----------|-------|
| `show_fields` | Fields returned in API responses | `"*"` = all fields | N/A (at least `id`) |
| `create_fields` | Fields allowed in POST requests | `"*"` = all fields | `[]` = cannot create |
| `update_fields` | Fields allowed in PUT/PATCH requests | `"*"` = all fields | `[]` = cannot update |
| `hidden_fields` | Fields explicitly removed from responses | N/A | `[]` = nothing hidden |

### How Permissions Generate Policy Code

```yaml
# This YAML:
analyst:
  actions: [index, show, store, update]
  show_fields: [id, title, status, tags]
  create_fields: [title, tags]
  update_fields: [title, tags]
  hidden_fields: [total_value, risk_score]
```

Generates this policy code:

```php
public function permittedAttributesForShow(?Authenticatable $user): array
{
    // ... other roles ...
    if ($this->hasRole($user, 'analyst')) {
        return ['id', 'title', 'status', 'tags'];
    }
    return [];
}

public function hiddenAttributesForShow(?Authenticatable $user): array
{
    if ($this->hasRole($user, 'analyst')) {
        return ['total_value', 'risk_score'];
    }
    return [];
}

public function permittedAttributesForCreate(?Authenticatable $user): array
{
    // ... other roles ...
    if ($this->hasRole($user, 'analyst')) {
        return ['title', 'tags'];
    }
    return [];
}
```

**Key: Roles with identical field sets are grouped** (e.g., `admin || manager`) to keep generated code clean.

---

## YAML Anchors — DRY Pattern

Use YAML anchors to avoid duplicating field lists:

```yaml
permissions:
  admin:
    actions: [index, show, store, update, destroy]
    create_fields: &admin_writable     # Define anchor
      - title
      - status
      - description
      - category
    update_fields: *admin_writable     # Reference anchor

  manager:
    actions: [index, show, store, update]
    create_fields: *admin_writable     # Same list as admin
    update_fields: *admin_writable
```

---

## Common Patterns

### Read-Only Model (no create/update/delete)

```yaml
options:
  except_actions: [store, update, destroy]

permissions:
  admin:
    actions: [index, show]
    show_fields: "*"
    create_fields: []
    update_fields: []
  viewer:
    actions: [index, show]
    show_fields: [id, title, status]
    create_fields: []
    update_fields: []
```

### Child Model (belongs to a parent, not organization)

```yaml
model: Comment
options:
  belongs_to_organization: false
  owner: post                        # scoped under Post model

columns:
  body: text
  post_id:
    type: foreignId
    foreign_model: Post
```

### Internal Model (no API endpoints)

If a model should not have API endpoints, don't create a blueprint file for it. Blueprints are only for API-exposed resources.

---

## Running the Generator

```bash
# Generate all models from blueprints
php artisan rhino:blueprint

# Process single model
php artisan rhino:blueprint --model=contracts

# Preview without writing files
php artisan rhino:blueprint --dry-run

# Force regeneration (ignore cached hashes)
php artisan rhino:blueprint --force

# Skip specific artifacts
php artisan rhino:blueprint --skip-tests
php artisan rhino:blueprint --skip-seeders

# Custom blueprint directory
php artisan rhino:blueprint --dir=.rhino/blueprints
```

### Re-running After Changes

The generator uses SHA-256 hashes to track changes. If a YAML file hasn't changed since last generation, it's skipped automatically. Use `--force` to bypass this.

**Important:** The generator will **overwrite** previously generated files. If you've manually edited a generated file, your changes will be lost on re-generation. Keep your changes in the YAML spec.

---

## Valid Actions

| Action | HTTP Method | Route | Description |
|--------|-------------|-------|-------------|
| `index` | GET | `/{slug}` | List all records |
| `show` | GET | `/{slug}/{id}` | Show single record |
| `store` | POST | `/{slug}` | Create new record |
| `update` | PUT/PATCH | `/{slug}/{id}` | Update record |
| `destroy` | DELETE | `/{slug}/{id}` | Soft delete record |
| `trashed` | GET | `/{slug}/trashed` | List soft-deleted |
| `restore` | POST | `/{slug}/{id}/restore` | Restore soft-deleted |
| `forceDelete` | DELETE | `/{slug}/{id}/force` | Permanently delete |

---

## Tips for AI Assistants

1. **Always read `_roles.yaml` first** to know available roles
2. **Ask about field visibility per role** — this is the most important part
3. **Use anchors** when 2+ roles share the same field list
4. **Owner role usually gets `"*"` wildcard** for all surfaces
5. **Viewer role usually gets `[]` for create/update** (read-only)
6. **Don't include `id`, `created_at`, `updated_at`** in columns — they're auto-generated
7. **Don't include `organization_id`** in columns — set `belongs_to_organization: true` instead
8. **Fields in `hidden_fields` are explicitly removed** even if they'd be in `show_fields: "*"`
9. **Validate your YAML** — the generator will reject invalid specs with clear error messages
10. **One file per model** — don't combine multiple models in one file
